1. Set Up the Environment

	# Installing Ruby, Rails, and Postgres
    
    # Creating the Rails Application
    	> rails new shinelinux --webpack --skip-turbolinks --skip-spring --skip-test -d postgresql
		> bundle exec rails webpacker:install
    	> configure the database
    	> create the db
    	> run the app

    # Create home page
    	> create dashboard controller with index action
		> add root route
		> modify index page
		> test it out 
		> :)
	
	# Setting Up Bootstrap with Yarn and Webpack
		> add gem foreman
		# package.json  
		> add webpack
		> yarn install
		> bundle exec rails webpacker:compile
		# 1_setup/20-install-webpack/shine/Procfile
		> create Procfile and add this:
			rails: bundle exec rails server
			./bin/webpack-dev-server
		# Create the file app/javascript/packs/application.css	
		> application.css + add font-family for html
		> import it to application.js
		> add js and style tags to app layout
			<%= javascript_pack_tag 'application' %>
		    <%= stylesheet_pack_tag 'application' %>
		> modify the layout
		> yarn add bootstrap@3
		> import bootstrap to application.js
		> foreman start	

    	Next: Authentication with Devise, Styled by Bootstrap